Introduction to LCM

We can retrieve data for a single person using id

ds<- dsL %>% 
  dplyr::filter(id==1,year %in% c(2000:2011)) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(time=year-2000) %>%
  dplyr::select(id,year,attend, time) 
print(ds)
   id year attend time
1   1 2000      1    0
2   1 2001      6    1
3   1 2002      2    2
4   1 2003      1    3
5   1 2004      1    4
6   1 2005      1    5
7   1 2006      1    6
8   1 2007      1    7
9   1 2008      1    8
10  1 2009      1    9
11  1 2010      1   10
12  1 2011      1   11

Or enter data manually, if we want to work with artificial trajectories

ds<- dsL %>% 
  dplyr::filter(id==1,year %in% c(2000:2011)) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(time=year-2000) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(attend= c(6,7,7,6,4,3,2,1,1,1,2,2)) %>%
  dplyr::select(id,year,attend,time)

attendF=ordered(ds$attend,
            levels= unique(dsL$attend,is.na=T),
            labels=levels(dsL$attendF))
print(ds)
   id year attend time
1   1 2000      6    0
2   1 2001      7    1
3   1 2002      7    2
4   1 2003      6    3
5   1 2004      4    4
6   1 2005      3    5
7   1 2006      2    6
8   1 2007      1    7
9   1 2008      1    8
10  1 2009      1    9
11  1 2010      2   10
12  1 2011      2   11

add a straight line to represent possible predition line, in this case a straight line

linear<- predict(lm(attend ~ time, ds))
ds<- ds %>% dplyr::mutate(linear=linear)
print(ds)
   id year attend time linear
1   1 2000      6    0 6.6923
2   1 2001      7    1 6.1119
3   1 2002      7    2 5.5315
4   1 2003      6    3 4.9510
5   1 2004      4    4 4.3706
6   1 2005      3    5 3.7902
7   1 2006      2    6 3.2098
8   1 2007      1    7 2.6294
9   1 2008      1    8 2.0490
10  1 2009      1    9 1.4685
11  1 2010      2   10 0.8881
12  1 2011      2   11 0.3077
p<-p+ geom_line(aes(y=linear),color="red", size=.5)
p

Or adding the curvarture the quadratic term

quadratic<- predict(lm(attend ~ poly(time,2),ds))
ds<- ds %>% mutate(quadratic=quadratic)
print(ds)
   id year attend time linear quadratic
1   1 2000      6    0 6.6923     7.764
2   1 2001      7    1 6.1119     6.599
3   1 2002      7    2 5.5315     5.551
4   1 2003      6    3 4.9510     4.620
5   1 2004      4    4 4.3706     3.806
6   1 2005      3    5 3.7902     3.108
7   1 2006      2    6 3.2098     2.528
8   1 2007      1    7 2.6294     2.064
9   1 2008      1    8 2.0490     1.718
10  1 2009      1    9 1.4685     1.488
11  1 2010      2   10 0.8881     1.375
12  1 2011      2   11 0.3077     1.379
p<-p+ geom_line(aes(y=quadratic),color="blue", size=.5)
 p

or the cubic term

cubic<- predict(lm(attend ~ poly(time,3),ds))
ds<- ds %>% mutate( cubic=cubic)
print(ds)
   id year attend time linear quadratic  cubic
1   1 2000      6    0 6.6923     7.764 6.4945
2   1 2001      7    1 6.1119     6.599 6.7143
